\end_inset

 (dashed line).
 For the figure we used 
\begin_inset Formula $\eta_{1}=\eta_{2}=1/2$
\end_inset

 and the following parameter values: (a) 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{1}=\pi/4$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{2}=2\pi/7$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{1}=3/4$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{2}=1/4$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{1}=3/4$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{2}=1/4$
\end_inset

; (b) 
\begin_inset Formula $\cos\theta_{1}=1/4\sqrt{3}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\cos\theta_{2}=1/4$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{1}=3/4$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{2}=1/4$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{1}=3/4$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{2}=1/4$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "Fig2"

\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset VSpace bigskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To get the expression of the total error rate as a function of FRIO, insert
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:Q1opt"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "Q2opt"

\end_inset

 into 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:PeTotal"

\end_inset

, 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
P_{E}=\left\{ \begin{array}{ll}
\frac{1}{2}\!\left\{ \left(1-Q\right)-\sqrt{(\omega_{1}-Q)^{2}-\left(\omega_{1}Q_{0,1}-Q\right)^{2}}-\sqrt{(\omega_{2})^{2}-\left(\omega_{2}Q_{0,2}\right)^{2}}\right\}  & \mbox{ if \ensuremath{Q_{th}^{(1)}\leq Q\leq Q_{th}^{(2)}}}\ ,\\
\frac{1}{2}\!\left\{ \left(1-Q\right)-\sqrt{(1-Q)^{2}-\left(Q_{0}-Q\right)^{2}}\right\}  & \mbox{ if \ensuremath{Q_{th}^{(2)}<Q\leq Q_{0}}}\ ,
\end{array}\right.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We will show that this is valid in all regions of the parameter 
\begin_inset Formula $Q$
\end_inset

.
 For 
\begin_inset Formula $Q=0$
\end_inset

 it reduces to the optimal Minimum Error expression for two subspaces 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Bergou2006"

\end_inset

, as it should.
 On the other hand for 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{e}=0$
\end_inset

 it reduces to the optimal Unambiguous Discrimination of two subspaces 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Herzog2005,Bergou2006a"

\end_inset

 We close this section by displaying 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{e,i}$
\end_inset

 vs.
 
\begin_inset Formula $Q$
\end_inset

 in Fig.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Fig3"

\end_inset

, for some specific values of the parameters.
\end_layout

