\begin_layout Standard
The results presented so far are valid if the parameters are such that in
 all subspaces we are in the POVM regime, i.e., 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{i}$
\end_inset

 is in the unshaded region (region II) of Fig.
 1 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

.
 When the parameters are such that in some subspaces we are in the projective
 regime, i.e., 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{i}$
\end_inset

 falls in the shaded regions of Fig.
 1 (regions I and III) for some 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 we have to modify the treatment to account for the fact that the error
 expression for the corresponding subspace, 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{e,i}$
\end_inset

, is no longer given by Eq.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "Pei2"

\end_inset

 but by 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "PeSol2Exp"

\end_inset

.
 We will study this case in the next section.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Projective regime
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have seen for the single subspace case that the POVM solution is valid
 if the inconclusive rate is smaller than a boundary value, 
\begin_inset Formula $Q\leq Q_{b}$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{b}$
\end_inset

 is given by Eq.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "Qb"

\end_inset

.
 With an obvious generalization, the POVM solution holds in subspace 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 if in that subspace 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{i}\leq Q_{b,i}$
\end_inset

 holds where the subspace boundary value is given by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
Q_{{\rm b,i}}\equiv{2\eta_{1,i}\eta_{2,i}\sin^{2}\theta_{i}/(1-Q_{0,i})}.\label{Qbi}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

%In Fig.
 
\backslash
ref{Fig6} we plot $Q_{
\backslash
rm c,i}$ and~$Q_{
\backslash
rm b,i}$ vs.~$
\backslash
eta_{1}$ together for a fixed overlap, %$
\backslash
cos
\backslash
theta = 0.5$ ($
\backslash
theta = 
\backslash
pi/3$).
 
\end_layout

\end_inset


