\begin_layout Standard
In the region 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{b,i}\leq Q_{i}\leq Q_{c,i}$
\end_inset

 the optimal measurement is a standard projective quantum measurement (SQM).
 The curves 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{b,i}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{c,i}$
\end_inset

 intersect at 
\begin_inset Formula $\eta_{1,i}=\eta_{1,i}^{(l)}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\eta_{1,i}=\eta_{1,i}^{(r)}$
\end_inset

, the same points as in Eq.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "Qmax"

\end_inset

.
 The interval 
\begin_inset Formula $0\leq\eta_{1,i}\leq1$
\end_inset

 is thus divided into three regions.
 In regions
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

I and
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

III, we have 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{{\rm b,i}}<Q_{{\rm c,i}}$
\end_inset

 and the solution
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "PeSol1"

\end_inset

 is valid for 
\begin_inset Formula $0\leq Q_{i}<Q_{{\rm b}}$
\end_inset

 only.
 In Region II, 
\begin_inset Formula $\eta_{1,i}^{(l)}\leq\eta_{1,i}\leq\eta_{1,i}^{(r)}$
\end_inset

, we have 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{{\rm c,i}}=Q_{0,i}<Q_{{\rm b,i}}$
\end_inset

 and the solution 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "PeSol1"

\end_inset

 is valid for the entire 
\begin_inset Formula $0\leq Q_{i}\leq Q_{{\rm c,i}}$
\end_inset

 range.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus, Fig.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Fig1"

\end_inset

 is valid in every subspace, with the obvious change of axis labels to 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{i}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\eta_{1,i}$
\end_inset

.
 So, 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{i}>Q_{b,i}$
\end_inset

 occurs in regions I and III and in the shaded areas the optimal FRIO measuremen
t is an SQM while in the unshaded area it is a POVM.
 We now illustrate the case when the FRIO measurement is a POVM in one and
 an SQM in the other subspace on an example.
 
