\begin_layout Standard
The optimal distribution of the total available inconclusive rate 
\begin_inset Formula $Q$
\end_inset

 between the two subspaces, 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{1}^{opt}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{2}^{opt}$
\end_inset

 such that their sum satisfies 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{1}^{opt}+Q_{2}^{opt}=Q$
\end_inset

, can be found by optimizing the total error rate with respect to the failure
 rate of the subspaces.
 We now have to use the error expression 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "PeSol2Exp"

\end_inset

 in subspace 1 for 
\begin_inset Formula $Q>Q_{b,1}$
\end_inset

.
 This leads to a numerical optimization problem, the result of which is
 shown in Fig.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Fig6"

\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

%
\backslash
subsection{Second elimination}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
placement ht
