\begin_inset Formula $\begin{array}{c}
\includegraphics[height=4cm]{Fig6.png}\end{array}$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Argument 1
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset space \hspace{}
\length 1cm
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{i}Q_{i}^{opt}$
\end_inset

 vs.
 
\begin_inset Formula $Q$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset

Optimal subspace failure rates 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{i}Q_{i}^{opt}$
\end_inset

 vs.
 
\begin_inset Formula $Q$
\end_inset

 from Eq.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "Qiopt"

\end_inset

, for two subspaces (
\begin_inset Formula $i=1,2,3$
\end_inset

).
 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{1}Q_{1}^{opt}$
\end_inset

: solid upper line.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{2}Q_{2}^{opt}$
\end_inset

: solid lower line.
 The dashed lines indicate the behavior of the corresponding quantities
 if the POVM solution were valid for subspace 1.
 For the figure we used 
\begin_inset Formula $\eta_{1}=\eta_{2}=1/2$
\end_inset

 and the following parameter values: 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{1}=\pi/16$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta_{2}=3\pi/7$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{1}=9/10$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{2}=1/10$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{1}=1/10$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{2}=9/10$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "Fig6"

\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The solution again exhibits a threshold structure.
 The dashed lines in the figure indicate how the optimal 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{i}$
\end_inset

's would behave if the POVM solution were valid for subspace 1 instead of
 the SQM.
 It is apparent that the SQM shifts the threshold toward a higher value
 of 
\begin_inset Formula $Q$
\end_inset

 and above the threshold the dependence on 
\begin_inset Formula $Q$
\end_inset

 is nonlinear, while for the POVM regime it is always linear.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The optimal inconclusive rate for subspace 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{i}^{opt}$
\end_inset

, displayed in Fig 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Fig6"

\end_inset

, is then inserted into Eq.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "PeSol2Exp"

\end_inset

 for 
\begin_inset Formula $i=1$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "Pei2"

\end_inset

 for 
\begin_inset Formula $i=2$
\end_inset

.
 This yields the optimal error rate for subspace 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{e,i}^{opt}$
\end_inset

.
 The results are displayed in Fig.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Fig7"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

